// WRONG: 'static means the value lives forever
// RIGHT: 'static means the type has no borrowed references
//        (or all references it has are also 'static)

// A String is 'static (owns its data)
// A &'static str is a reference that happens to live forever
// An &str with any lifetime is NOT 'static

